Day 26 Answers (ArrayList Practice Level 2)

Question 1: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme 5 numbers daal lo. Fir 3rd index wala element print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(10);
list.add(20);
list.add(30);
list.add(40);
list.add(50);
System.out.println("3rd index wala element: " + list.get(3));

Question 2: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme 5 numbers daal lo. Fir 2nd index wala element ko update karke usme 100 set karo aur poori list print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(5);
list.add(15);
list.add(25);
list.add(35);
list.add(45);
list.set(2, 100);
System.out.println(list);

Question 3: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme se koi specific element (jaise 10) ko remove karo aur list print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(10);
list.add(20);
list.add(30);
list.add(40);
list.add(50);
list.remove(Integer.valueOf(10));
System.out.println(list);

Question 4: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme 5 numbers daal lo. Fir check karo ki list empty hai ya nahi aur print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(1);
list.add(2);
list.add(3);
list.add(4);
list.add(5);
System.out.println("List empty hai kya? " + list.isEmpty());

Question 5: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme 5 numbers daal lo. Fir usme se saare elements ko clear karo aur size print karo

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(10);
list.add(20);
list.add(30);
list.add(40);
list.add(50);
list.clear();
System.out.println("Size of list after clear: " + list.size());

Question 6: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme kuch numbers daal lo. Fir har element ko index ke saath print karo. (jaise: Index 0 ka element 5 hai).

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(11);
list.add(22);
list.add(33);
list.add(44);
list.add(55);
for(int i = 0; i < list.size(); i++){
    System.out.println("Index " + i + " ka element: " + list.get(i));
}

Question 7: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme se sabhi elements ko double karke ek nayi ArrayList me daalo aur nayi list print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(2);
list.add(4);
list.add(6);
list.add(8);
list.add(10);
ArrayList<Integer> doubledList = new ArrayList<>();
for(int num : list){
    doubledList.add(num * 2);
}
System.out.println(doubledList);

Question 8: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme 5 numbers daal lo. Fir maximum aur minimum element print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(13);
list.add(7);
list.add(21);
list.add(5);
list.add(19);
int max = list.get(0);
int min = list.get(0);
for(int num : list){
    if(num > max) max = num;
    if(num < min) min = num;
}
System.out.println("Max: " + max);
System.out.println("Min: " + min);

Question 9: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme 5 numbers daal lo. Fir sum calculate karke print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(10);
list.add(20);
list.add(30);
list.add(40);
list.add(50);
int sum = 0;
for(int num : list){
    sum += num;
}
System.out.println("Sum: " + sum);

Question 10: Ek ArrayList bana lo aur usme se har even element ko remove karo aur list print karo.

ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(1);
list.add(2);
list.add(3);
list.add(4);
list.add(5);
list.removeIf(element -> element % 2 == 0);
System.out.println(list);
